      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED BULL BERNIE (7) has the hoof on the till after finishing runner-up in both outings at this circuit and distance since some good efforts during the Gold Chalice series. Came from one spot wider and worked when beaten just over a metre last week. With better fortune he can atone. MAC THUNDER (5) was held up last time but not disgraced there and there was merit in the prior effort for second at Penrith. Race fit and this looks a suitable assignment. TIME TO DANCE NZ (10) may need some luck from the back row but was a solid fourth at his most recent appearance at Penrith and is proven at this circuit and distance. SATELLITE EXPRESS (3) kicked off his career with a win a week ago, coming from a wider barrier and getting home by a head at this circuit and distance. Rises in grade but draws well and has some upside.",
